<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="390" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,223,574]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,223,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Distribution:</emphasis>
Known only from the Venezuelan and Colombian plains, in the Orinoco River basin (
<bibRefCitation author="Molina, C. &amp; Senaris, J. C. &amp; Ayarzaguena, J." pageId="13" pageNumber="390" pagination="485 - 491" refId="ref17501" refString="Molina, C., Senaris, J. C. &amp; Ayarzaguena, J. (2002) Contribution to the Knowledge of the Taxonomy, Distribution, and Natural History of Leposoma hexalepis (Reptilia: Gymnophthalmidae) in Venezuela. Herpetologica, 58 (4), 485 - 491. https: // doi. org / 10.1655 / 0018 - 0831 (2002) 058 [0485: CTTKOT] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2002">
Molina 
<emphasis box="[1379,1437,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[261,371,259,285]" name="Colombia" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Colombia</collectingCountry>
from the 
<collectingRegion box="[480,705,259,285]" country="Colombia" name="Vichada" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Vichada department</collectingRegion>
in the northeast Orinoquia (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1111,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution maps for the cis-Andean microteiid lizards in Colombia (Alopoglossidae + Gymnophthalmidae). Circles are examined specimens, while squares are records from literature (see Supplementary Files for specific references). Red arrows indicate new records for Colombia. Black arrows show a zoom in to regions where several records overlap. The light green shadow indicates the Orinoco River basin, and the dark green the Amazon River basin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5681929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5681929/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,223,574]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,387,295,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Similar species:</emphasis>
Although 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ayala &amp; Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[509,748,295,321]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hexalepis">
<emphasis box="[509,748,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Loxopholis hexalepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be allopatric from other cis-Andean species in 
<collectingCountry name="Colombia" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, it can be distinguished from these in having hexagonal dorsal scales (rhomboid in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esqueda" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[1155,1307,332,357]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caparensis">L. caparensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1886" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parietalis">L. parietalis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[237,417,368,393]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis box="[237,417,368,393]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; hexagonal to quadranglar or lanceolate in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[896,1058,367,393]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[896,1058,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); smooth ventral scales (keeled in 
<emphasis box="[151,489,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[151,291,403,429]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parietalis">L. parietalis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[302,485,404,429]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">L. percarinatum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[543,707,403,429]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[543,707,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); fourth pair of chin-shields reduced (not reduced in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[1300,1436,403,429]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parietalis">
<emphasis box="[1300,1436,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. parietalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[198,362,439,465]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[198,362,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and 32–36 scales around midbody (
<quantity box="[782,882,439,465]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.239" metricValueMax="7.62" metricValueMin="6.858" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" unit="in" value="28.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="27.0">27–30 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esqueda" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[889,1038,440,465]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caparensis">
<emphasis box="[889,1038,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. caparensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity box="[1052,1151,439,465]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="6.858" metricValueMin="5.842" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" unit="in" value="25.0" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="23.0">23–27 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1886" box="[1158,1294,439,465]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parietalis">
<emphasis box="[1158,1294,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L. parietalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity box="[1308,1407,439,465]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.476999999999999" metricValueMax="6.858" metricValueMin="6.096" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" unit="in" value="25.5" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="24.0">24–27 in</quantity>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">L. percarinatum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<quantity box="[364,463,475,501]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="6.604" metricValueMin="6.096" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" unit="in" value="25.0" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="24.0">24–26 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[470,633,475,502]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[470,486,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[499,633,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). For a more detailed description see 
<bibRefCitation author="Molina, C. &amp; Senaris, J. C. &amp; Ayarzaguena, J." box="[1056,1285,475,501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" pagination="485 - 491" refId="ref17501" refString="Molina, C., Senaris, J. C. &amp; Ayarzaguena, J. (2002) Contribution to the Knowledge of the Taxonomy, Distribution, and Natural History of Leposoma hexalepis (Reptilia: Gymnophthalmidae) in Venezuela. Herpetologica, 58 (4), 485 - 491. https: // doi. org / 10.1655 / 0018 - 0831 (2002) 058 [0485: CTTKOT] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2002">
Molina 
<emphasis box="[1144,1200,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="390" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,223,574]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,511,537]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">Remarks:</emphasis>
In the species redescription, 
<bibRefCitation author="Molina, C. &amp; Senaris, J. C. &amp; Ayarzaguena, J." box="[637,859,511,537]" pageId="13" pageNumber="390" pagination="485 - 491" refId="ref17501" refString="Molina, C., Senaris, J. C. &amp; Ayarzaguena, J. (2002) Contribution to the Knowledge of the Taxonomy, Distribution, and Natural History of Leposoma hexalepis (Reptilia: Gymnophthalmidae) in Venezuela. Herpetologica, 58 (4), 485 - 491. https: // doi. org / 10.1655 / 0018 - 0831 (2002) 058 [0485: CTTKOT] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2002">
Molina 
<emphasis box="[724,779,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
stated (
<emphasis box="[945,1031,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="390">in error</emphasis>
) that the dorsal scales of this species are pentagonal, but their illustrations and the original description indicate they are hexagonal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
